<li id="lithub_daily_widget-9" class="widget widget_lithub_daily_widget"><div class="lithub-daily-header"><a href="/category/lit-hub-daily/"><b>Lithub</b> Daily</a></div><h2 class="widgettitle">May 6, 2024</h2>
<a href="https://lithub.com/lit-hub-daily-may-6-2024/"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-236701 size-thumbnail" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/A_notebook-150x150.jpg" alt="notebook and pencil" width="150" height="150" /></a>
<ul>
 	<li><a href="https://www.thenation.com/article/archive/wkcr-columbia-media-coverage/" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">In praise of the student journalists covering university protests</span></a></li>
 	<li><a href="https://theoffingmag.com/insight/my-love-poems-are-the-most-palestinian-thing-about-me/" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">Mandy Shunnarah on Mahmoud Darwish and writing Palestinian poetry</span></a></li>
 	<li><a href="https://lareviewofbooks.org/article/im-only-interested-in-the-real-a-conversation-between-rachel-cusk-and-ira-sachs/" class="external" target="_blank">Rachel Cusk and Ira Sachs discuss “novelistic” filmmaking</a></li>
</ul>
